	   <tr><td colspan=2>I won the roll on an Icereaver last night. It has the exact base delay as the mith 2 hander, 40, so I figured I could use it to calculate the M2H's haste. I targeted a guard and stepped away until I couldn't hit it. I turned off all incoming chat, and hit my attck hotkey. I counted the number of &quot;You are too far away....&quot; messages I got in one minute. The counting was made easier by hitting my Sense Heading hotkey every 5 messages to break up the endless block of red text. The average number of times I got the message after 5 runs with each sword are:<br><br>Icereaver: 33 attempted swings<br>Mithril 2 Hander: 43 attempted swings<br><br>So, 43 - 33 = 10 extra swings attempted every minute, and 10/33 = .3 or 30% haste making this weapon 21/28 and VERY good. <br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Dec 15 14:58:22 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Banvaren Holybane<br>38 Paladin <br>Povar Server</td></tr>
